---
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "South Korea Work Visa Insurance Guide 2026 | E-7 Visa & NHIS Requirements";
const description = "Complete guide to South Korea work visa insurance requirements. Covers E-7 Special Activities visa, NHIS enrollment, and health coverage for working in Korea.";

const tocItems = [
  { id: "overview", label: "Overview" },
  { id: "quick-decision", label: "Is This Right for You?" },
  { id: "official-requirements", label: "Official Requirements" },
  { id: "insurance-requirements", label: "Insurance Requirements" },
  { id: "recommended-providers", label: "Recommended Providers" },
  { id: "costs", label: "Costs Breakdown" },
  { id: "application-timeline", label: "Application Timeline" },
  { id: "scenarios", label: "Real-World Scenarios" },
  { id: "common-mistakes", label: "Common Mistakes" },
  { id: "healthcare-access", label: "Healthcare Access" },
  { id: "faq", label: "FAQs" },
  { id: "verdict", label: "Final Verdict" }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <PageShell
    title="South Korea Work Visa Insurance Guide"
    subtitle="Your complete guide to working legally in South Korea with proper health coverage"
    heroImage="/images/countries/south-korea-hero-bg.png"
    tocItems={tocItems}
  >
    <!-- Quick Facts Box -->
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-4">Quick Facts: South Korea Work Visa</h3>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div><strong>Main Visa Type:</strong> E-7 (Special Activities/Skilled Worker)</div>
        <div><strong>Initial Duration:</strong> 1-3 years (renewable)</div>
        <div><strong>Salary Requirement:</strong> GNI per capita (~₩42M/year) for some categories</div>
        <div><strong>Processing Time:</strong> 2-4 weeks</div>
        <div><strong>Health Insurance:</strong> NHIS mandatory (employer-enrolled)</div>
        <div><strong>PR Pathway:</strong> F-5 after 5+ years (F-2-7 points system available)</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Overview -->
    <section id="overview" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Overview</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        South Korea has transformed into a major destination for skilled foreign workers, particularly in technology, engineering, and education. The E-7 (Special Activities) visa is the primary pathway for professionals, covering 85+ designated occupations from software developers to foreign language instructors at companies.
      </p>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Korea's National Health Insurance Service (NHIS) provides universal coverage, and all employed foreigners are automatically enrolled through their employers. The system covers approximately 70% of medical costs with low copays, making healthcare remarkably affordable. Quality is excellent—Korea is a global leader in medical technology and has one of the highest hospital bed ratios in the world.
      </p>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        The work culture can be intense, with long hours common in many industries. However, recent labor reforms and the growing influence of global companies are gradually shifting expectations. Korean language ability, while not visa-required, significantly impacts both career progression and daily life quality.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Quick Decision Guide -->
    <section id="quick-decision" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Is a South Korea Work Visa Right for You?</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Good Fit If You...</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Have a job offer from a Korean company</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Work in tech, engineering, or education</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Interested in Korean culture and willing to learn language</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Want excellent, affordable healthcare</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Have relevant degree matching job field</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives If...</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You prioritize work-life balance (long hours culture)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You won't learn any Korean (daily life challenging)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>Your occupation isn't on the E-7 eligible list</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You lack a degree in your job field</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You have difficulty with hierarchical work environments</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Official Requirements -->
    <section id="official-requirements" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Official Requirements</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">E-7 Visa Categories</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Category", "Occupations", "Salary Requirement", "Duration"]}
        rows={[
          ["E-7-1 (Professionals)", "Managers, executives, researchers", "Above GNI per capita", "1-3 years"],
          ["E-7-2 (Semi-professionals)", "Engineers, IT specialists, designers", "At or above GNI per capita", "1-3 years"],
          ["E-7-3 (Office Workers)", "Administrative, accounting, marketing", "Above GNI per capita", "1-2 years"],
          ["E-7-4 (Skilled Workers)", "Technicians, specialized manufacturing", "Minimum wage + premium", "1-3 years"]
        ]}
      />

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
        <p class="text-blue-800 font-medium">GNI Per Capita Reference (2025)</p>
        <p class="text-blue-700 text-sm mt-1">Korea's GNI per capita is approximately ₩42,000,000/year (~$32,000). E-7-1 and E-7-3 require salaries above this threshold. Check the latest Immigration Ministry announcement for current figures.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Eligibility Requirements</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Requirement", "Details", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Job Offer", "From Korean registered company", "Contract required"],
          ["Relevant Degree", "Bachelor's+ in related field", "Must match job duties"],
          ["Work Experience", "Typically 1+ years", "Can substitute for degree in some cases"],
          ["Occupation List", "Must be on E-7 eligible occupations", "85+ occupations currently"],
          ["Company Quota", "Large companies have easier approval", "SMEs may face more scrutiny"],
          ["Criminal Record", "Clean background", "Apostilled police certificate"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Required Documents</h3>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Valid passport</strong> – At least 6 months validity</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Visa application form</strong> – Form 34 completed</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Employment contract</strong> – Original, stating position and salary</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Degree certificate</strong> – Apostilled, with Korean or English translation</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Career certificates</strong> – Previous employment verification</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Company documents</strong> – Business registration, tax records</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Photo</strong> – 3.5cm × 4.5cm, recent</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Criminal record check</strong> – Apostilled, from home country</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Insurance Requirements -->
    <section id="insurance-requirements" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Insurance Requirements</h2>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
        <p class="text-green-800 font-medium">✓ NHIS Enrollment is Mandatory and Automatic</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 text-sm mt-1">All employees in Korea are automatically enrolled in the National Health Insurance Service (NHIS) through their employer. Coverage begins from your employment start date. Contributions are split between employee (~3.545%) and employer (~3.545%).</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">How Korean Health Insurance Works</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Component", "Coverage", "Your Cost"]}
        rows={[
          ["NHIS (건강보험)", "Medical care, hospital, prescriptions", "~3.545% of salary + copays"],
          ["Long-term Care (장기요양)", "Elderly/disabled care", "~0.43% of salary"],
          ["Industrial Accident", "Work-related injuries", "Employer pays 100%"],
          ["Employment Insurance", "Unemployment benefits", "~0.9% of salary"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">NHIS Coverage and Copays</h3>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        NHIS typically covers 60-80% of medical costs, with patients paying 20-40% as copay. Hospital stays have lower copays than outpatient care. The system is remarkably affordable—a typical doctor visit costs ₩5,000-15,000 (~$4-12) after insurance.
      </p>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Service", "NHIS Coverage", "Your Copay"]}
        rows={[
          ["Clinic (의원) visit", "70%", "30% (~₩5,000-15,000)"],
          ["Hospital outpatient", "60%", "40%"],
          ["Hospital inpatient", "80%", "20%"],
          ["Prescription drugs", "70%", "30%"],
          ["Dental (basic)", "Limited", "50-70%"],
          ["Dental (cosmetic/orthodontics)", "Not covered", "100%"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">What's Not Covered</h3>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Covered by NHIS</h4>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• Doctor consultations</li>
            <li>• Hospital stays</li>
            <li>• Surgery</li>
            <li>• Prescriptions</li>
            <li>• Basic dental (extractions, fillings)</li>
            <li>• Maternity care</li>
            <li>• Mental health (basic)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Not Covered/Limited</h4>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• Private hospital rooms</li>
            <li>• Cosmetic procedures</li>
            <li>• Orthodontics</li>
            <li>• Vision (glasses, LASIK)</li>
            <li>• Advanced dental (implants, crowns)</li>
            <li>• Alternative medicine</li>
            <li>• Some specialized treatments</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
        <p class="text-amber-800 font-medium">Private Insurance for Gaps</p>
        <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm mt-1">Many Koreans and expats add private insurance (실손보험) to cover the 20-40% copay and non-covered items. Plans cost ₩50,000-150,000/month and reimburse most out-of-pocket medical expenses.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Recommended Providers -->
    <section id="recommended-providers" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
        NHIS provides excellent core coverage. Many expats add Korean private insurance (실손보험) for copay coverage or international insurance for global coverage and English support.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Korean Private Insurers (실손보험)</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Insurer", "Plan Type", "Monthly Cost", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Samsung Life", "Comprehensive medical", "₩50,000-100,000", "Largest Korean insurer"],
          ["Hanwha Life", "Medical + accident", "₩40,000-90,000", "Good expat options"],
          ["Kyobo Life", "실손 + critical illness", "₩50,000-120,000", "Strong hospital network"],
          ["DB Insurance", "Medical reimbursement", "₩30,000-80,000", "Budget-friendly"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">International Providers</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Provider", "Best For", "Annual Cost", "Key Features"]}
        rows={[
          ["Cigna Global", "Executives, global coverage", "$2,500-6,000", "Direct billing, English support"],
          ["BUPA Global", "Mental health needs", "$2,200-5,500", "No therapy limits"],
          ["Allianz Care", "European expats", "$2,000-5,000", "Strong Asia network"],
          ["Now Health", "Asia-focused expats", "$1,800-4,500", "Good Korea network"],
          ["SafetyWing", "Short-term/nomads", "$600-1,200", "Budget supplemental"]
        ]}
      />

      <CTABox
        title="Compare Health Insurance for South Korea"
        description="Find supplemental coverage to complement your NHIS enrollment and cover gaps."
        buttonText="Compare Plans"
        buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
      />
    </section>

    <!-- Costs Breakdown -->
    <section id="costs" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Costs Breakdown</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Visa & Setup Costs</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Item", "Cost (KRW)", "Cost (USD)", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["E-7 Visa fee", "₩60,000-130,000", "$45-100", "Varies by nationality/duration"],
          ["Alien Registration Card", "₩30,000", "$23", "Mandatory within 90 days"],
          ["Document apostille", "₩50,000-200,000", "$40-150", "Home country costs vary"],
          ["Document translation", "₩30,000-100,000", "$23-75", "If not in Korean/English"],
          ["Health check (if required)", "₩50,000-100,000", "$40-75", "Some employers require"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Monthly Deductions</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Item", "Employee Rate", "Employer Rate", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["NHIS (Health)", "3.545%", "3.545%", "Split 50/50"],
          ["National Pension", "4.5%", "4.5%", "Refundable if leaving Korea"],
          ["Employment Insurance", "0.9%", "1.15-1.75%", "Unemployment benefits"],
          ["Long-term Care", "0.43%", "0.43%", "Part of NHIS contribution"],
          ["Income Tax", "6-45%", "N/A", "Progressive rates"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Living Costs (Monthly)</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Category", "Seoul", "Other Cities", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Rent (Studio/1BR)", "₩800,000-2,000,000", "₩400,000-1,000,000", "Jeonse deposit system alternative"],
          ["Utilities", "₩100,000-200,000", "₩80,000-150,000", "Heating expensive in winter"],
          ["Transport", "₩60,000-100,000", "₩50,000-80,000", "Excellent subway system"],
          ["Food", "₩400,000-800,000", "₩300,000-600,000", "Eating out is affordable"],
          ["Healthcare (OOP)", "₩30,000-100,000", "₩30,000-100,000", "Copays are low"]
        ]}
      />

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
        <p class="text-blue-800 font-medium">Jeonse Housing System</p>
        <p class="text-blue-700 text-sm mt-1">Korea has a unique "jeonse" system where you pay a large deposit (often 50-80% of property value) instead of monthly rent. The landlord invests your deposit and returns it when you leave. This can save significant money long-term if you have the upfront capital.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Application Timeline -->
    <section id="application-timeline" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Timeline</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 1-2</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Document Preparation</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Gather documents: apostilled degree, criminal record check, employment verification. Get translations if needed. Employer prepares company documents and employment contract.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 2-3</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Visa Application</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Apply at Korean embassy/consulate in your country. Submit all documents and pay visa fee. Some countries offer online application through VISA Portal.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 3-6</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Processing</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Embassy forwards application to Korean Immigration. Processing typically 2-4 weeks. May request additional documents. Large company sponsorships often process faster.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 6-7</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Visa Issuance & Entry</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Receive visa sticker in passport. Enter Korea within visa validity period. E-7 visa allows immediate work authorization.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Day 1-90</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Alien Registration</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Register at local Immigration Office within 90 days. Receive Alien Registration Card (ARC). ARC needed for banking, phone contracts, NHIS card. Employer handles NHIS enrollment from first day.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Real-World Scenarios -->
    <section id="scenarios" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Software Engineer at Samsung</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">David, 29, CS degree from US university. Recruited directly by Samsung. E-7-2 visa processed in 3 weeks. ₩65M salary. NHIS covers almost everything—paid ₩8,000 for doctor visit with prescription. Company also provides private insurance.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Large company = smooth process, excellent benefits</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">English Teacher Transitioning to Tech</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Sarah, 32, had E-2 teaching visa for 3 years. Self-taught programming, got job at startup. Needed to change visa status to E-7. Process took 6 weeks—Immigration questioned relevance of English degree to tech role. Eventually approved with experience documentation.</p>
          <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Visa change possible but required extra justification</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Designer at Small Agency</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Mia, 27, graphic design degree. Hired by 15-person design agency. Immigration scrutinized small company more carefully. Required additional proof of company financials and genuine need for foreign hire. Took 5 weeks but approved.</p>
          <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: SMEs face more scrutiny but approval still possible</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">F-2-7 Points-Based Residency</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Chen, 35, worked 4 years on E-7. Passed TOPIK Level 4, earned ₩70M salary, has master's degree. Scored 85 points on F-2-7 system (need 80). Now has F-2-7 residence visa with work flexibility and path to F-5 permanent residence.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: F-2-7 points system rewards long-term residents</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Healthcare Experience</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Tom, 40, needed MRI for back pain. Walked into hospital, got MRI same day. Total cost: ₩180,000 (~$140) after NHIS. In home country would have waited weeks and paid $2,000+. Added Korean 실손보험 that reimbursed his copay.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Korean healthcare is fast, high-quality, and affordable</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Degree Mismatch Rejection</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Alex, 26, psychology degree but applying for marketing role. Immigration rejected—degree didn't match job category sufficiently. Had to find role more aligned with degree or gain more relevant work experience first.</p>
          <p class="text-red-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Degree-job alignment strictly enforced</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Common Mistakes -->
    <section id="common-mistakes" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">1. Not Getting Alien Registration Card Within 90 Days</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">You must register at Immigration and get your ARC within 90 days of arrival. Without ARC, you can't open bank accounts, get phone contracts, or receive your NHIS card. Late registration results in fines.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">2. Degree Not Matching Job Field</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Korean Immigration strictly enforces degree-job relevance. An unrelated degree will likely result in rejection. If your degree doesn't match, you'll need extensive work experience (typically 5+ years) to compensate.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">3. Forgetting to Report Job Changes</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">If you change employers, you must notify Immigration within 15 days and apply for visa status update. Working for a new employer without updating your visa is illegal and can result in deportation.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">4. Not Understanding Pension Refund</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Your National Pension contributions are refundable when you permanently leave Korea (if your country has a pension agreement with Korea). Apply at the National Pension Service before departure. Many expats forget and lose this money.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">5. Assuming English is Sufficient</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">While many companies use English, daily life, healthcare interactions, and government offices often require Korean. Learning at least basic Korean significantly improves quality of life. TOPIK certification also helps with visa upgrades.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Healthcare Access -->
    <section id="healthcare-access" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Healthcare System Access</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Korea's healthcare system is excellent and accessible. There's no GP gatekeeper—you can visit any clinic or hospital directly. Wait times are short, quality is high, and costs after NHIS coverage are remarkably low. The system may feel transactional compared to Western healthcare, but efficiency is outstanding.
      </p>

